            <abstract>
                <p>This text is attested as part of several works circulating under the label 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">Zenā nagaromu la-śǝllāse</foreign> (taken from its first phrase).</p>
                <p>It is attested as introduction of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1300Dersan"/> (for example in 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="ESum001"/> or <ref type="mss" corresp="EMIP02056"/>), a collection 
                    of homilies for each month followed by c. 60 miracles of the Trinity.
                </p>
                <p>It is also attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr62 "/> as part of a collection of prayers and seven miracles of
                    the 
                    Trinity arranged according to the days of the week (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT7331SaySelColl"/>), and possibly also in 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy015"/> as part of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2296Sayfas"/>.</p>
            </abstract>
